div.p:
"And again, verily I say unto you . . . that my servant Hyrum may take the office of
Priesthood and Patriarch, which was appointed unto him by his father, by blessing and also by
right;

"That he may act in concert also with my servant Joseph; and that he shall receive counsel
from my servant Joseph, who shall show unto him the keys whereby he may ask and receive,
and be crowned with the same blessing, and glory, and honor, and priesthood, and gifts of the
priesthood, that once were put upon him that was my servant Oliver Cowdery;
